The paper deals with the Steiner Tree Problem in Graphs (STP), which is a well-studied problem in computer science. The paper presents a new class of instances for STP and analyzes the integrality gap of the bidirected cut relaxation, which is a well-known LP-relaxation for STP. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, graph theory, and optimization, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.LG, and cs.CC.
